sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. (NYSE:NOTE) Not Doing Enough For Some Investors As Its Shares Slump 33%
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings (NYSE:NOTE) has seen its shares drop significantly, with a 33% decline in the last month and an 83% fall over the past year. Despite a low price-to-sales (P/S) ratio of 0.3x, analysts express concern over the company's declining revenue, which was down 18% last year and is forecast to contract further by 5.7% in the coming year, contrasting with the broader industry's expected growth. This poor revenue performance is seen as the underlying reason for the low P/S and continued investor skepticism.

feed.title: FiscalNote: director Hwang sells shares worth $10.7k By Investing.com
feed.summary: FiscalNote director Tim Hwang sold shares totaling $10.7k to cover tax obligations related to restricted stock units, pre-arranged under a Rule 10b5-1 trading plan. The company's stock is currently trading near its 52-week low despite impressive gross profit margins, operating with significant debt, and not being profitable over the last twelve months. FiscalNote recently reported Q3 2025 earnings meeting revenue guidance and exceeding adjusted EBITDA expectations, alongside introducing new features and expanding customer partnerships for its AI-driven policy intelligence solutions.

feed.title: FiscalNote updates executive contracts and approves retention awards
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. has amended employment agreements for its CEO, Josh Resnik, and CFO, Jon Slabaugh, and approved one-time cash retention awards of $500,000 and $300,000, respectively. These awards are contingent on 48 months of continued employment. Additionally, the company updated its Change in Control Severance Plan, which now excludes its principal executive and financial officers.

feed.title: FiscalNote Introduces AI-Powered Bill Comparison in PolicyNote - The Joplin Globe
feed.summary: FiscalNote has launched "Bill Comparison" within its PolicyNote platform, a new AI-powered feature enabling users to quickly compare legislative documents and track changes. This tool helps policy professionals analyze differences between bill versions, related legislation, or stakeholder briefings in seconds, overcoming the tedious manual review process. The feature is part of FiscalNote's broader suite of AI-driven capabilities designed to provide deep insights, such as identifying language reuse and policy themes across jurisdictions, thereby accelerating strategic decision-making in a complex policy environment.

feed.title: FiscalNote Receives Continued Listing Notice From NYSE
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. (NYSE: NOTE) announced it received a notice from the NYSE regarding non-compliance with the minimum average closing share price requirement of $1.00 over 30 trading days. The company, which is otherwise compliant with NYSE standards, has a six-month period to regain compliance. FiscalNote is evaluating options, focusing on operational efficiencies, debt reduction, platform migration, and strengthening customer KPIs while its stock continues to trade on the NYSE.

feed.title: FiscalNote Regains Compliance With NYSE Continued Listing Standard
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. announced it has regained compliance with the NYSE continued listing standard for minimum share price. The company's common stock had a closing share price of at least $1.00 and maintained an average closing share price of at least $1.00 over a 30 trading-day period. This achievement allows FiscalNote to continue trading on the NYSE and reinforces its commitment to profitable growth and shareholder value.

feed.title: FiscalNote Holdings Faces NYSE Delisting Notice Challenge
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings (NOTE) received a delisting notice from the NYSE because its stock price fell below $1.00 for 30 consecutive trading days. The company has a six-month period to regain compliance and is exploring options to meet the listing requirements. Its operations, investor engagement, and stock listing are not immediately impacted.

feed.title: FiscalNote Announces Can Babaoglu as Chief Product Officer to Accelerate AI-Powered Product Innovation, Customer Engagement, and Product-Led Growth
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. has appointed Can Babaoglu as Chief Product Officer. Babaoglu will lead the company's product roadmap, strategy, and vision, leveraging FiscalNote's AI and data science strengths to enhance existing products and launch new ones. His extensive experience includes spearheading the development of CoCounsel, the world's first AI legal assistant, at Casetext.

feed.title: Empowered Systems and FiscalNote Announce Strategic Partnership to Expand and Enhance Third-Party Risk Management Solutions
feed.summary: Empowered Systems and FiscalNote announced a strategic partnership to integrate FiscalNote’s Risk Connector, Copilot for Global Intelligence, and Dragonfly into Empowered Systems' Connected Risk™ platform. This collaboration aims to create an unparalleled third-party risk management solution, leveraging AI-powered insights and global intelligence to help businesses navigate complex risk environments and enhance resilience. The partnership is expected to expand FiscalNote's customer base and accelerate growth by delivering critical insights to risk and compliance teams.

feed.title: FiscalNote Reports Second Quarter 2024 Financial Results
feed.summary: FiscalNote reported strong second-quarter 2024 financial results, exceeding previous forecasts with $29.2 million in total revenues and $1.8 million in adjusted EBITDA, marking its fourth consecutive quarter of positive adjusted EBITDA. The company continues to accelerate its AI product strategy, launching new AI Copilot solutions and strategic partnerships, while also raising its full-year adjusted EBITDA forecast. FiscalNote's Board of Directors is reviewing strategic options to maximize shareholder value and anticipates accelerated growth rates in 2025 through product innovation and improved customer experience.

feed.title: FiscalNote Announces New Strategic Partnership with Creolytix, Integrating its Dragonfly Offering with Creolytix’s Platform
feed.summary: FiscalNote Holdings, Inc. announced a strategic distribution partnership between its Dragonfly Security Intelligence & Analysis Service and Creolytix’s managed security services platform. This collaboration aims to provide small to mid-sized companies in the European marketplace, particularly the DACH region, with integrated geopolitical and security intelligence via a SaaS-enabled platform for enhanced risk management. This partnership follows FiscalNote's recent launch of its Global Intelligence AI Copilot, further strengthening its offerings in navigating geopolitical and regulatory risks.

feed.title: FiscalNote Shares Soar 75% After Getting Tapped as ChatGPT’s Launch Partner
feed.summary: FiscalNote (NOTE) shares surged approximately 75% after OpenAI selected the global policy and market intelligence provider as a launch partner for its ChatGPT plugin. This collaboration will allow FiscalNote to integrate its legal, political, and regulatory data directly into the generative AI platform, enhancing its analytical capabilities. Analysts are optimistic about FiscalNote's future, with BTIG maintaining a "buy" rating and a $7 price target due to encouraging guidance and improved investor communication.

feed.title: FiscalNote Completes Acquisition of Aicel Technologies
feed.summary: FiscalNote (NYSE: NOTE) has completed its acquisition of Aicel Technologies, a South Korea-based alternative data company. This acquisition enhances FiscalNote’s AI data offerings, expands its global reach, particularly in the APAC region, and strengthens its presence in the fintech and financial services industries. Aicel's expertise in AI, data transformation, and its proprietary datasets are expected to drive new revenue opportunities and bolster FiscalNote's decision intelligence capabilities.

feed.title: Duddell Street Acquisition Corp. and FiscalNote Complete Business Combination
feed.summary: Duddell Street Acquisition Corp. and FiscalNote have completed their business combination, with FiscalNote's Class A common stock and warrants set to begin trading on the NYSE under the symbols "NOTE" and "NOTE WS" on August 1, 2022. This move is expected to enhance FiscalNote's growth strategy in the public markets, supported by a $425 million long-term growth plan. FiscalNote's Co-Founder, Chairman, and CEO, Tim Hwang, will ring the NYSE Opening Bell on August 4, 2022, to celebrate the public trading debut.
